tells us that we can learn things we

00:23:35.200 --> 00:23:40.559
never thought we could learn

00:23:37.440 --> 00:23:42.880
simply by going online

00:23:40.559 --> 00:23:45.200
julius also shows us some very

00:23:42.880 --> 00:23:47.120
perceptive approaches to learning wealth

00:23:45.200 --> 00:23:48.400
that we can apply in our own learning

00:23:47.120 --> 00:23:50.720
and teaching

00:23:48.400 --> 00:23:52.320
what do i mean by this

00:23:50.720 --> 00:23:54.400
let's take a moment and look at the

00:23:52.320 --> 00:23:56.559
history of education

00:23:54.400 --> 00:23:58.640
for thousands of years a typical

00:23:56.559 --> 00:24:01.840
approach to teaching in school was just

00:23:58.640 --> 00:24:05.120
to stand up there and lecture for hours

00:24:01.840 --> 00:24:07.600
and this made sense it makes sense even

00:24:05.120 --> 00:24:09.279
right now you're watching a lecture here

00:24:07.600 --> 00:24:11.840
as i speak

00:24:09.279 --> 00:24:14.480
we can't sit around the table together

00:24:11.840 --> 00:24:16.080
much as i would love to and converse in

00:24:14.480 --> 00:24:18.400
person

00:24:16.080 --> 00:24:21.520
but in general going on for many hours

00:24:18.400 --> 00:24:24.240
at a time is perhaps not as effective an

00:24:21.520 --> 00:24:26.960
approach as it could be in teaching

00:24:24.240 --> 00:24:30.320
teachers begin to realize

00:24:26.960 --> 00:24:34.080
starting maybe 30 to 40 years ago that

00:24:30.320 --> 00:24:36.559
active learning can be very very

00:24:34.080 --> 00:24:39.200
beneficial in learning

00:24:36.559 --> 00:24:42.400
so it became a popular notion

00:24:39.200 --> 00:24:44.400
very nearly a fad that students only

00:24:42.400 --> 00:24:45.679
learn the material when they're actively

00:24:44.400 --> 00:24:48.320
looking on it

00:24:45.679 --> 00:24:50.799
so all of a sudden teaching became swept

00:24:48.320 --> 00:24:53.760
up in this idea that active learning was

00:24:50.799 --> 00:24:57.360
the only way that students learn

00:24:53.760 --> 00:25:00.240
but what is active learning really

00:24:57.360 --> 00:25:01.200
often it involves only a superficial

00:25:00.240 --> 00:25:04.720
notion

00:25:01.200 --> 00:25:07.200
of how student brains actually learn

00:25:04.720 --> 00:25:10.159
i mean you've already seen here that

00:25:07.200 --> 00:25:12.559
retrieval practice which is generally

00:25:10.159 --> 00:25:14.960
and rightly considered a part of active

00:25:12.559 --> 00:25:18.400
learning is very important

00:25:14.960 --> 00:25:20.799
but a student has to get those sets of

00:25:18.400 --> 00:25:23.760
neural links at least weekly in place

00:25:20.799 --> 00:25:26.720
before they have anything to retrieve

00:25:23.760 --> 00:25:29.919
in other words guidance from a teacher

00:25:26.720 --> 00:25:33.120
from pages of a book or the pixels of a

00:25:29.919 --> 00:25:36.159
video are still necessary to get

00:25:33.120 --> 00:25:38.480
students started in their initial

00:25:36.159 --> 00:25:41.360
placement of sets of links involving the

00:25:38.480 --> 00:25:44.880
material into the brain

00:25:41.360 --> 00:25:47.440
so at least some explicit explanation

00:25:44.880 --> 00:25:48.720
from teachers along with active practice

00:25:47.440 --> 00:25:51.520
by students

00:25:48.720 --> 00:25:54.240
are necessary for learning

