mixed with active practice and that's

00:27:30.399 --> 00:27:35.760
how he became an expert in throwing the

00:27:32.880 --> 00:27:39.440
javelin but what does this all mean from

00:27:35.760 --> 00:27:42.320
a neuroscientific perspective

00:27:39.440 --> 00:27:44.880
i've mentioned that we create sets of

00:27:42.320 --> 00:27:45.919
links in long-term memory when we learn

00:27:44.880 --> 00:27:48.559
anything

00:27:45.919 --> 00:27:49.679
but what i didn't mention was that there

00:27:48.559 --> 00:27:52.000
are two

00:27:49.679 --> 00:27:55.360
different pathways that these sets of

00:27:52.000 --> 00:27:57.039
links can be deposited into long-term

00:27:55.360 --> 00:27:59.840
memory

00:27:57.039 --> 00:28:02.399
the first pathway involves taking the

00:27:59.840 --> 00:28:04.159
information we receive

00:28:02.399 --> 00:28:07.039
from working memory

00:28:04.159 --> 00:28:08.000
as it passes through the hippocampus

00:28:07.039 --> 00:28:09.600
into

00:28:08.000 --> 00:28:12.320
long-term memory

00:28:09.600 --> 00:28:14.720
this is called the declarative pathway

00:28:12.320 --> 00:28:18.399
it's called declarative because we can

00:28:14.720 --> 00:28:22.159
declare it we're consciously aware of it

00:28:18.399 --> 00:28:25.039
this passes through the hippocampus

00:28:22.159 --> 00:28:28.159
there's a completely different pathway

00:28:25.039 --> 00:28:29.600
though called the procedural pathway

00:28:28.159 --> 00:28:32.559
and this

00:28:29.600 --> 00:28:34.640
goes through the basal ganglia

00:28:32.559 --> 00:28:37.120
we're often not conscious of things

00:28:34.640 --> 00:28:39.840
we've learned procedurally for example

00:28:37.120 --> 00:28:41.760
you may make use of

00:28:39.840 --> 00:28:44.559
the patterns of your native language

00:28:41.760 --> 00:28:47.520
without even being conscious of them

00:28:44.559 --> 00:28:51.200
because you've learned them procedurally

00:28:47.520 --> 00:28:54.240
as it turns out both declarative and

00:28:51.200 --> 00:28:56.840
procedural sets of links are what allow

00:28:54.240 --> 00:29:00.000
us to learn well and excel in what we're

00:28:56.840 --> 00:29:03.120
learning what do i mean by that

00:29:00.000 --> 00:29:06.159
i mean that the links deposited by each

00:29:03.120 --> 00:29:07.520
system can have very very different

00:29:06.159 --> 00:29:09.840
characteristics

00:29:07.520 --> 00:29:11.520
and you need both types of links to be

00:29:09.840 --> 00:29:14.720
able to be fast

00:29:11.520 --> 00:29:17.760
intuitive and flexible in whatever you

00:29:14.720 --> 00:29:21.360
or your students are learning

00:29:17.760 --> 00:29:23.440
now declarative learning as it turns out

00:29:21.360 --> 00:29:26.000
can develop through conscious

00:29:23.440 --> 00:29:27.919
explanation so you're conscious for

00:29:26.000 --> 00:29:29.440
example of what i'm explaining here

00:29:27.919 --> 00:29:31.039
right now

00:29:29.440 --> 00:29:32.720
procedural learning on the other hand

00:29:31.039 --> 00:29:34.960
develops through

00:29:32.720 --> 00:29:38.000
lots of practice

00:29:34.960 --> 00:29:40.640
practice solving theorems practice tying

00:29:38.000 --> 00:29:43.039
your shoelaces practice playing a song

00:29:40.640 --> 00:29:44.880
on the piano skateboarding or speaking a

00:29:43.039 --> 00:29:47.919
new language

00:29:44.880 --> 00:29:50.640
procedurally learned information is

00:29:47.919 --> 00:29:52.320
unusual in that you can't explain it

00:29:50.640 --> 00:29:54.799
very easily

00:29:52.320 --> 00:29:56.640
if you know how to solve a rubik's cube

00:29:54.799 --> 00:29:59.520
for example you

00:29:56.640 --> 00:30:01.200
may or may not be able to explain how

00:29:59.520 --> 00:30:03.679
you can solve it

00:30:01.200 --> 00:30:06.159
but you can still solve it

00:30:03.679 --> 00:30:08.720
and indeed many children can learn

00:30:06.159 --> 00:30:12.640
really well procedurally even though

00:30:08.720 --> 00:30:13.440
they can't learn that well declaratively

00:30:12.640 --> 00:30:15.520
so

00:30:13.440 --> 00:30:17.440
for example

00:30:15.520 --> 00:30:19.919
those on the autistic spectrum can

00:30:17.440 --> 00:30:22.799
sometimes learn incredibly well and

00:30:19.919 --> 00:30:25.200
swiftly by learning procedurally

00:30:22.799 --> 00:30:29.440
but if you ask them to stop and explain

00:30:25.200 --> 00:30:31.120
every step declaratively well that's not

00:30:29.440 --> 00:30:33.279
the way they learned

00:30:31.120 --> 00:30:36.080
you can actually kill these students

00:30:33.279 --> 00:30:39.600
interest and desire in learning by

00:30:36.080 --> 00:30:42.720
making them stop and use only the

00:30:39.600 --> 00:30:43.840
declarative approach to explain whatever

00:30:42.720 --> 00:30:46.320
they're learning

00:30:43.840 --> 00:30:49.279
because that's not how they learned

00:30:46.320 --> 00:30:51.120
again it's the expert reversal effect

00:30:49.279 --> 00:30:52.559
where walking back through what you

00:30:51.120 --> 00:30:54.799
already know well

00:30:52.559 --> 00:30:56.320
can kill desire and motivation for

00:30:54.799 --> 00:30:58.480
learning

00:30:56.320 --> 00:31:01.919
the procedural system is often thought

00:30:58.480 --> 00:31:03.679
of as only involving that awful

00:31:01.919 --> 00:31:06.640
rote learning

00:31:03.679 --> 00:31:09.039
but in reality it's at the heart of our

00:31:06.640 --> 00:31:12.320
ability to understand and work with

00:31:09.039 --> 00:31:14.159
incredibly complex patterns like that of

00:31:12.320 --> 00:31:16.080
your native language which you learn

00:31:14.159 --> 00:31:19.039
procedurally

00:31:16.080 --> 00:31:21.120
the beauty of the procedural system is

00:31:19.039 --> 00:31:24.480
that once you've learned something

00:31:21.120 --> 00:31:26.559
through it no matter how complex it is

00:31:24.480 --> 00:31:29.120
you don't need to worry about it anymore

00:31:26.559 --> 00:31:31.679
because your procedural systems thinking

00:31:29.120 --> 00:31:34.720
and problem solving is all done below

00:31:31.679 --> 00:31:37.679
the level of conscious awareness

00:31:34.720 --> 00:31:40.960
one can't help but wonder that when it

00:31:37.679 --> 00:31:44.080
came to fairman's last theorem

00:31:40.960 --> 00:31:45.279
a to the n plus b to the n is equal to c

00:31:44.080 --> 00:31:48.320
to the n

00:31:45.279 --> 00:31:51.440
fermat saw in a procedural system

00:31:48.320 --> 00:31:53.679
intuitive glance the way to solve the

00:31:51.440 --> 00:31:58.080
problem

00:31:53.679 --> 00:32:00.880
but it took 250 years for the equation

00:31:58.080 --> 00:32:03.039
to be proved declaratively

00:32:00.880 --> 00:32:05.279
step by step

00:32:03.039 --> 00:32:07.679
it's generally very slow to learn

00:32:05.279 --> 00:32:08.960
proceed lately and it can take a lot of

00:32:07.679 --> 00:32:11.200
practice

00:32:08.960 --> 00:32:13.519
it takes a long time to learn to type

00:32:11.200 --> 00:32:16.000
for example but it's very fast once

00:32:13.519 --> 00:32:16.799
you've learned to type

00:32:16.000 --> 00:32:20.320
but

00:32:16.799 --> 00:32:23.600
procedural learning is also inflexible

00:32:20.320 --> 00:32:26.000
so for example if my mischievous husband

00:32:23.600 --> 00:32:27.679
went and rewired the different keys on

00:32:26.000 --> 00:32:30.960
the keyboard it would take me a long

00:32:27.679 --> 00:32:33.840
time to relearn how to type

00:32:30.960 --> 00:32:37.039
each neural pathway declarative as well

00:32:33.840 --> 00:32:39.519
as procedural has its advantages and

00:32:37.039 --> 00:32:41.600
disadvantages in the types of links it

00:32:39.519 --> 00:32:44.320
lays into place

00:32:41.600 --> 00:32:45.840
but both types of links can underpin

00:32:44.320 --> 00:32:48.080
good learning

00:32:45.840 --> 00:32:51.360
keep in mind however that if we try to

00:32:48.080 --> 00:32:54.559
fit every student into a box where they

00:32:51.360 --> 00:32:57.760
must learn for example declaratively by

00:32:54.559 --> 00:32:59.679
parroting back rote explanations we want

00:32:57.760 --> 00:33:02.880
them to feed back to us

00:32:59.679 --> 00:33:04.399
we can kill students interest and desire

00:33:02.880 --> 00:33:07.360
in learning

00:33:04.399 --> 00:33:09.360
in fact we can erroneously give a high

00:33:07.360 --> 00:33:12.320
grade to a student who doesn't

00:33:09.360 --> 00:33:14.640
understand how to do a problem at all

00:33:12.320 --> 00:33:17.440
just because the student can parrot back

00:33:14.640 --> 00:33:19.600
an explanation we want them to give

00:33:17.440 --> 00:33:22.320
where on the other hand we may give low

00:33:19.600 --> 00:33:25.440
marks to a student who knows how to

00:33:22.320 --> 00:33:27.679
solve problems intuitively and correctly

00:33:25.440 --> 00:33:30.640
but who can't parrot back the

00:33:27.679 --> 00:33:32.640
declarative explanation a teacher might

00:33:30.640 --> 00:33:35.440
demand

00:33:32.640 --> 00:33:38.640
interestingly there's evidence that some

00:33:35.440 --> 00:33:41.440
students can have an inclination

00:33:38.640 --> 00:33:43.519
to learn more declaratively

00:33:41.440 --> 00:33:46.799
while other students can have an

00:33:43.519 --> 00:33:48.960
inclination to learn more procedurally

00:33:46.799 --> 00:33:52.480
for example it seems that those with

00:33:48.960 --> 00:33:55.760
dyslexia can have a strong tendency to

00:33:52.480 --> 00:33:59.039
learn declaratively because there may be

00:33:55.760 --> 00:34:02.240
challenge with some aspects

00:33:59.039 --> 00:34:04.399
of their procedural learning system

00:34:02.240 --> 00:34:08.000
on the other hand some students on the

00:34:04.399 --> 00:34:10.720
autistic spectrum may have particularly

00:34:08.000 --> 00:34:13.839
pronounced and talented procedural

00:34:10.720 --> 00:34:15.599
systems in other words they learn best

00:34:13.839 --> 00:34:16.399
procedurally

00:34:15.599 --> 00:34:18.800
so

00:34:16.399 --> 00:34:20.960
perhaps these sorts of differences are

00:34:18.800 --> 00:34:23.200
what teachers are observing when they

00:34:20.960 --> 00:34:24.879
feel that students have different styles

00:34:23.200 --> 00:34:26.320
of learning

00:34:24.879 --> 00:34:29.200
now

00:34:26.320 --> 00:34:31.040
each system may provide

00:34:29.200 --> 00:34:33.520
distinct gifts when it becomes

00:34:31.040 --> 00:34:35.440
particularly strengthened as it is in

00:34:33.520 --> 00:34:39.119
some students with seeming disorders

00:34:35.440 --> 00:34:42.560
such as dyslexia and autistic spectrum

00:34:39.119 --> 00:34:45.679
in fact this may be why some nobel prize

