this team expectations agreement can

00:49:05.920 --> 00:49:09.920
help students to sign off on their

00:49:08.240 --> 00:49:12.319
expectations

00:49:09.920 --> 00:49:14.559
signing off together on expectations

00:49:12.319 --> 00:49:17.119
prevents situations where a student can

00:49:14.559 --> 00:49:19.760
claim to have not known what they were

00:49:17.119 --> 00:49:22.800
supposed to be doing or how they can

00:49:19.760 --> 00:49:25.920
contact other students on the team

00:49:22.800 --> 00:49:28.480
this form evaluation of progress towards

00:49:25.920 --> 00:49:31.119
effective team functioning

00:49:28.480 --> 00:49:33.599
allows students to get a sense of how an

00:49:31.119 --> 00:49:36.079
optimal team should be functioning

00:49:33.599 --> 00:49:38.400
including checks to see if their team is

00:49:36.079 --> 00:49:39.920
meeting on time whether they're quickly

00:49:38.400 --> 00:49:41.680
getting on task

00:49:39.920 --> 00:49:42.960
and whether they're listening to one

00:49:41.680 --> 00:49:46.319
another

00:49:42.960 --> 00:49:48.000
this peer reading of team members form

00:49:46.319 --> 00:49:50.400
allows teams

00:49:48.000 --> 00:49:52.960
to evaluate one another

00:49:50.400 --> 00:49:55.280
of course this form once it's filled out

00:49:52.960 --> 00:49:56.960
is for your eyes only

00:49:55.280 --> 00:49:59.599
you might be surprised to learn that one

00:49:56.960 --> 00:50:01.839
of the most useful aspects of this form

00:49:59.599 --> 00:50:04.319
is that it allows you to see how some

00:50:01.839 --> 00:50:07.440
students are exceptionally helpful

00:50:04.319 --> 00:50:10.160
behind the scenes where you can't see

00:50:07.440 --> 00:50:14.079
above all it's important to remember as

00:50:10.160 --> 00:50:15.280
my own work on pathological altruism has

00:50:14.079 --> 00:50:18.240
shown

00:50:15.280 --> 00:50:19.440
that over emphasis on the value of

00:50:18.240 --> 00:50:22.960
empathy

00:50:19.440 --> 00:50:24.559
can end up reaching only the already

00:50:22.960 --> 00:50:26.880
empathic

00:50:24.559 --> 00:50:29.680
this can lead to these sensitive

00:50:26.880 --> 00:50:32.960
individuals being taken advantage of and

00:50:29.680 --> 00:50:38.079
bullied and also lead these already kind

00:50:32.960 --> 00:50:40.480
students towards lives of codependency

00:50:38.079 --> 00:50:43.680
let's turn now to an exceptionally

00:50:40.480 --> 00:50:46.240
important idea which as cognitive

00:50:43.680 --> 00:50:48.319
psychologist dan willingham notes with

00:50:46.240 --> 00:50:51.520
his book by that name

00:50:48.319 --> 00:50:53.839
when can you trust the experts

00:50:51.520 --> 00:50:55.760
how can you tell good science from bad

00:50:53.839 --> 00:50:58.240
in education

00:50:55.760 --> 00:51:01.119
as willingham notes educators fall

00:50:58.240 --> 00:51:03.119
primarily into two groups

00:51:01.119 --> 00:51:05.839
those who understand the world through

00:51:03.119 --> 00:51:08.720
reason and those who understand the

00:51:05.839 --> 00:51:11.280
world through experience

00:51:08.720 --> 00:51:13.359
if we look carefully these ideas seem to

00:51:11.280 --> 00:51:16.480
relate to declarative learning as

00:51:13.359 --> 00:51:17.920
opposed to experiential procedural kind

00:51:16.480 --> 00:51:20.640
of learning

00:51:17.920 --> 00:51:23.520
in fact if we look more closely

00:51:20.640 --> 00:51:24.640
we could say that willingham's objective

00:51:23.520 --> 00:51:25.680
reason

00:51:24.640 --> 00:51:27.680
that is

00:51:25.680 --> 00:51:31.200
declarative learning

00:51:27.680 --> 00:51:33.760
is a little bit like this blue box here

00:51:31.200 --> 00:51:36.480
it's going through the hippocampus

00:51:33.760 --> 00:51:39.119
remember we're at least partly conscious

00:51:36.480 --> 00:51:41.280
of what's going on in the working memory

00:51:39.119 --> 00:51:43.760
and onward through the hippocampus as

00:51:41.280 --> 00:51:47.040
declarative learning proceeds logically

00:51:43.760 --> 00:51:51.200
step by step through the hippocampus

00:51:47.040 --> 00:51:54.319
whereas experience that is procedural

00:51:51.200 --> 00:51:57.520
learning is something like this this

00:51:54.319 --> 00:52:00.400
gray box of the basal ganglia

00:51:57.520 --> 00:52:03.760
procedural learning then is sort of a

00:52:00.400 --> 00:52:05.920
misty fog or we're not conscious of its

00:52:03.760 --> 00:52:08.559
influence no matter how profound that

00:52:05.920 --> 00:52:10.800
influence might be

00:52:08.559 --> 00:52:13.839
but there is a difference between these

00:52:10.800 --> 00:52:17.760
two approaches which involves the

00:52:13.839 --> 00:52:19.920
complex nature of the basal ganglia

00:52:17.760 --> 00:52:21.359
now i shouldn't imply that the

00:52:19.920 --> 00:52:25.040
hippocampus

00:52:21.359 --> 00:52:27.680
this hippocampus here is simple

00:52:25.040 --> 00:52:29.760
but we're conscious of our thinking when

00:52:27.680 --> 00:52:31.520
we're using declarative

00:52:29.760 --> 00:52:34.400
hippocampal thinking

00:52:31.520 --> 00:52:36.880
and in this sense it's simpler so if

00:52:34.400 --> 00:52:39.920
we're thinking along here we can think

00:52:36.880 --> 00:52:42.480
logically step by step and we're

00:52:39.920 --> 00:52:45.200
conscious of what we're thinking

00:52:42.480 --> 00:52:46.880
but with this basal ganglia procedural

00:52:45.200 --> 00:52:49.119
learning on the other hand

00:52:46.880 --> 00:52:53.040
we're not conscious

00:52:49.119 --> 00:52:55.599
of this extremely complex system

00:52:53.040 --> 00:52:58.319
this type of learning through the basal

00:52:55.599 --> 00:53:01.119
ganglia develops through plenty of

00:52:58.319 --> 00:53:03.359
practice over and over again so that's

00:53:01.119 --> 00:53:05.920
how you learn to hit a ball or how to

00:53:03.359 --> 00:53:07.680
solve a rubik's cube how you speak your

00:53:05.920 --> 00:53:09.760
native language

00:53:07.680 --> 00:53:12.480
whatever you're learning that is

00:53:09.760 --> 00:53:15.440
processed through the basal ganglia

00:53:12.480 --> 00:53:17.680
generally involves non-conscious

00:53:15.440 --> 00:53:20.640
procedural learning

00:53:17.680 --> 00:53:22.720
now also this procedural system develops

00:53:20.640 --> 00:53:24.559
what's called a

00:53:22.720 --> 00:53:26.880
value function

00:53:24.559 --> 00:53:30.160
this value function develops around what

00:53:26.880 --> 00:53:32.800
is ultimately found to be most rewarding

00:53:30.160 --> 00:53:36.079
in other words the value function of the

00:53:32.800 --> 00:53:38.640
procedural system is like a nest

00:53:36.079 --> 00:53:40.800
of hidden thinking about what is deemed

00:53:38.640 --> 00:53:43.520
optimal for you in the long run

00:53:40.800 --> 00:53:45.680
based on thousands and thousands of

00:53:43.520 --> 00:53:48.720
previous experiences

