01:07:15.359 --> 01:07:20.640
terrible student

01:07:17.440 --> 01:07:21.640
but this former loser of a student made

01:07:20.640 --> 01:07:24.400
such

01:07:21.640 --> 01:07:27.359
extraordinary scientific breakthroughs

01:07:24.400 --> 01:07:29.359
that he was awarded the nobel prize

01:07:27.359 --> 01:07:31.680
but even more impressive

01:07:29.359 --> 01:07:33.680
kahal is now known as the father of

01:07:31.680 --> 01:07:35.280
modern neuroscience

01:07:33.680 --> 01:07:37.119
he was asked

01:07:35.280 --> 01:07:40.160
how did you succeed

01:07:37.119 --> 01:07:43.680
and he said well i was persistent

01:07:40.160 --> 01:07:46.079
in other words he practiced a lot

01:07:43.680 --> 01:07:48.319
but the second thing he said was that he

01:07:46.079 --> 01:07:51.839
was flexible

01:07:48.319 --> 01:07:53.760
as he said i have worked with many

01:07:51.839 --> 01:07:57.119
geniuses

01:07:53.760 --> 01:07:59.839
and i was no genius and he was not

01:07:57.119 --> 01:08:02.079
but he said the problem with geniuses is

01:07:59.839 --> 01:08:03.920
that they can jump to conclusions and

01:08:02.079 --> 01:08:06.720
then when they're wrong

01:08:03.920 --> 01:08:10.319
they can't change their minds

01:08:06.720 --> 01:08:13.200
they simply use their intellects to find

01:08:10.319 --> 01:08:15.599
a way to justify why they must have been

01:08:13.200 --> 01:08:17.759
right after all

01:08:15.599 --> 01:08:20.400
over and over again we are seeing that

01:08:17.759 --> 01:08:22.960
technological advances in some areas

01:08:20.400 --> 01:08:25.440
such as calculators and search engines

01:08:22.960 --> 01:08:27.040
are actually hindering progress in

01:08:25.440 --> 01:08:29.359
education

01:08:27.040 --> 01:08:31.440
educators without a solid understanding

01:08:29.359 --> 01:08:35.040
of how the brain actually learns can

01:08:31.440 --> 01:08:37.520
inadvertently and sometimes inflexibly

01:08:35.040 --> 01:08:39.040
promote approaches that can hinder

01:08:37.520 --> 01:08:41.759
rather than help

01:08:39.040 --> 01:08:44.719
students abilities to learn

01:08:41.759 --> 01:08:47.199
but you on the other hand

01:08:44.719 --> 01:08:48.560
have watched this talk all the way

01:08:47.199 --> 01:08:50.880
through

01:08:48.560 --> 01:08:53.040
i hope with an open mind and a

01:08:50.880 --> 01:08:55.440
willingness to bring solid recent

01:08:53.040 --> 01:08:58.960
insights from neuroscience and cognitive

01:08:55.440 --> 01:09:01.600
psychology into education

01:08:58.960 --> 01:09:03.679
it is you who will help bring our

01:09:01.600 --> 01:09:06.080
students to the future

01:09:03.679 --> 01:09:09.199
you have my deepest thanks and the

01:09:06.080 --> 01:09:11.839
thanks of like-minded educators

01:09:09.199 --> 01:09:17.080
and the thanks of the many students you

01:09:11.839 --> 01:09:17.080
will impact in the years to come

01:09:26.400 --> 01:09:28.480
you